          <mj-image
              src="assets/staff-carrie-besnette-hauser-signature_black.png"
              alt="Signature Image"
              width="228px"
              padding="0 0 10px"
              align="left"
              css-class="dark-only"
          />
          <mj-raw><!--<![endif]--></mj-raw>
          <mj-text font-size="16px" padding="0">
            <p style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">
              Carrie Besnette-Hauser
              <br />
              <em style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Placeholder title, Example Division</em>
              <br />
              <b>Trust for Public Land</b>
            </p>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-group>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- END: Signature Card (original) -->

    <!-- START: Footer -->
    <mj-section
      css-class="footer-block block"
      background-color="#000000"
      padding="60px 20px 0"
      full-width="full-width"
    >
      <mj-column width="480px">
        <mj-image
          alt="Logo"
          src="assets/logo-tpl_color-light-green-text.png"
          width="150px"
          href="https://www.example.com"
        />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section
      css-class="footer-block block"
      background-color="#000000"
      padding="30px 20px 0"
      full-width="full-width"

    >
      <mj-group width="480px">
        <mj-column width="33%" vertical-align="middle">
          <mj-text
            padding="0"
            css-class="footer-text"
            color="#ffffff"
          >
            <p style="text-align: center;">
              <a style="letter-spacing:2px;color:#ffffff;font-weight:bold;text-decoration: none" href="#">DONATE</a>
            </p>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
        <mj-column width="66%"  border-left="2px solid #4d4d4d" vertical-align="middle">
          <mj-text
            padding="0"
            css-class="footer-text"
            color="#ffffff"
          >
            <p style="text-align: center;">
              <a style="letter-spacing:2px;color:#ffffff;font-weight:bold;text-decoration: none" href="#">MANAGE SUBSCRIPTION</a>
            </p>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-group>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section
        css-class="footer-block block"
        background-color="#000000"
        padding="0 20px 60px"
        full-width="full-width"

    >
      <mj-column width="480px">
        <mj-text
          padding="30px 0 0"
          css-class="footer-text"
          color="#ffffff"
        >
          <p>
            Photos by:  Anand Varma, Wallace W. Nutting, Tamara Merino, Photo Ark: ANIMALS OF EARTH
            by Joel Sartore, Exhibit Rendering, Michael O. Snyder / Preserving Legacies,
            Joel Sartore / Trust for Public Land Photo Ark
          </p>
          <p>
            The Trust for Public Land is a nonprofit organization driven by the belief in the
            power of science, exploration, and storytelling to change the world. The Trust for Public Land
            Society is a 501(c)(3), tax-exempt organization. Copyright © 2025 Trust for Public Land.
            All rights reserved.
          </p>
          <p>
            <br />
            You are receiving this email because you elected to receive marketing communications from
            Trust for Public Land under the terms of our Privacy Policy and Terms of Service.
          </p>
          <p>
            You may unsubscribe from this list if you no longer wish to receive email marketing
            communications. If you would like to unsubscribe from ALL email communication from Trust for
            Public Land, request erasure or portability of your personal data please email
            donor.outreach@tpl.org with your request.
          </p>
          <p>
            You may not be able to save the whole world, but you can make a difference in your own
            backyard by planting a garden with native plants to provide a sustainable habitat for local
            pollinators and other wildlife.
          </p>
